@felixcheung You're right! `evaluate` is dependency package of `knitr`.
Thanks for pointing out. It's my misunderstood. 
Let me close this PR.

@zjffdu I agree about bringing security related features together in longer term, possibly `Credentials` menu could be used for that. 
Also regarding previously discussed running of `--proxy-user` with yarn cluster mode, I believe it's currently not supported in Zeppelin. As far as I know only standalone and yarn-client modes are supported by pure Spark interpreter.
@Tagar right, if used in that way, kerberos tickets wouldn't be renewed automatically. However as i said, I think Spark interpreter doesn't support yarn cluster mode, so using `ZEPPELIN_IMPERSONATE_CMD` with `kinit` wouldn't be required in that case. 

also anyone having yarn cluster mode setup with kerberos is more than welcome to test it :)

Sorry, I was not able to work on this issue during last weeks.
@AhyoungRyu, I will make the corrections soon.
Thanks

@jongyoul small amount of :) 

if you want to reduce time more for `npm install`, you can use `yarn install` instead of. It will decrease 20~50 secs. ([install before using it](https://yarnpkg.com/en/docs/install))
And https://github.com/apache/zeppelin/pull/1812 was merged recently so it is applied to `zeppelin-web` module now.

@Leemoonsoo Thanks for review! 

If https://github.com/apache/zeppelin/pull/1874 is merged soon, I can rewrite the whole `conda env *` commands based on #1874 
since current implementation requires some custom formatting for `env list`.

I improved the template of html because I think `customHome` html and `Home` html should be equally worked when `home` js controller is changed. 
So, I changed from the template in `home.html` to template of `customHome.html`.

@AhyoungRyu @Leemoonsoo could you check this PR again, please?
